                            <comment id="52557" author="niu" created="Sun, 17 Feb 2013 01:36:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patches landed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="51298" author="niu" created="Sun, 27 Jan 2013 23:26:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch for b2_1: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5184&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5184&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50649" author="niu" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2013 05:01:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5050&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5050&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50646" author="niu" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2013 04:31:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The OBD_FAIL_PTLRPC_CLIENT_BULK_CB will result in rq_net_error set on the request, and trigger reconnect immediately... I think the test script needs be improved as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50644" author="yujian" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2013 04:04:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre Branch: b1_8&lt;br/&gt;
Lustre Build: &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b1_8/242&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b1_8/242&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue still occurred: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/327f6338-5ffb-11e2-84d4-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/327f6338-5ffb-11e2-84d4-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The above build contains patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4964&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4964&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50394" author="niu" created="Sun, 13 Jan 2013 23:03:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch for master: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5012&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5012&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50051" author="niu" created="Mon, 7 Jan 2013 04:17:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch for b1_8: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4964&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4964&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50050" author="niu" created="Mon, 7 Jan 2013 04:11:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test in master(&amp;amp; b2_1) doesn&apos;t have &apos;sync&apos; after dd, I think that&apos;s why this bug isn&apos;t triggered in master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50049" author="niu" created="Mon, 7 Jan 2013 02:13:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks there is something wrong in the resend: in osc_brw_redo_request(), each time we rebuild a request, but never increase the aa_resends for the new request, so the io request will be resent infinitely if it always get -EIO (in this test). I&apos;m wondering why it happened only on b_8? b2_1 &amp;amp; master should have the same problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50044" author="pjones" created="Sun, 6 Jan 2013 11:28:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Niu&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50041" author="yujian" created="Sun, 6 Jan 2013 08:56:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another instance on Lustre b1_8 branch:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/00323a48-5774-11e2-8772-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/00323a48-5774-11e2-8772-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50038" author="yujian" created="Sun, 6 Jan 2013 07:21:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue can be reproduced on Lustre b1_8 build #236:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/c8649180-57a3-11e2-8b17-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/c8649180-57a3-11e2-8b17-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49804" author="yujian" created="Sun, 30 Dec 2012 21:52:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a regression issue on Lustre b1_8 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
